#ROOMS

#610
The Blighted Gateway~
The massive iron gates of Kel'Shadra loom before you, twisted and
blackened as if scorched by some unimaginable flame. Beyond them,
a path of crushed obsidian winds into darkness. The air here carries
the taste of ash and the faint whisper of countless lost souls. Pale
violet light pulses from cracks in the gate's ancient frame, and the
stones around the entrance are covered in dark runes that seem to
shift and rearrange whenever you look away.
~
8201 11
D1
~
~
0 -1 611
D3
~
~
0 -1 615
E gate~
The iron gate bears countless ancient runes. You recognize some as
wards against the living, others as bindings to prevent whatever is
inside from escaping. Someone - or something - has partially broken
several of the wards from the inside.
~
S

#611
The Obsidian Courtyard~
This courtyard was once an assembly area for Kel'Shadra's forces. Cracked
black flagstones line the ground, each one engraved with a name in a dead
language. The walls rise sharply on three sides, their surfaces studded
with extinguished torch sconces shaped like screaming faces. In the center
of the courtyard, a fountain of some dark, viscous liquid gurgles slowly.
Whatever it was made to hold, it is no longer water.
~
