smells of nothing at all. Where it touches the stone basin, the stone
has turned black and cracked. You sense that drinking from it would be
very unwise.
~
S

#612
The Northern Hall~
A long corridor stretches before you, its ceiling lost in shadow far
above. Tattered black banners hang motionless from the walls despite
a constant cold draft, as if the wind itself fears to disturb them.
Between the banners, iron sconces hold torches that burn with cold
blue flame, casting deep shadows that seem to have shapes of their own.
~
