The gem is embedded deeply in the wall and cannot be removed without
shattering it. It pulses with a slow, rhythmic light - almost like breathing.
~
S

#615
The Western Passage~
This passage runs parallel to the main entrance but curves away into
deeper darkness. The floor here is noticeably colder than the courtyard,
and frost crystals have formed along the base of the walls. Ahead, the
passage narrows significantly. Something large has clearly been dragged
through here recently - claw marks and dark stains mark the floor.
~
