#617
The Corrupted Chapel~
What was once a place of dark worship has been further defiled. Pews of
black wood have been smashed and thrown against the walls. At the far end,
an altar of void-stone still stands, but something is wrong with it - the
air above it shimmers with barely contained energy that crackles and hisses.
Candles of black wax burn in skull-shaped holders, their flames producing
no warmth whatsoever.
~
