gradually evolve toward more modern writing. The most recent names are
from people you might recognize. The very last name scratched appears
to have been left unfinished - only the first three letters carved before
whatever was doing the carving stopped.
~
S

#620
The Armory of Ashes~
This chamber once served as an armory, but most of its contents have been
reduced to cinders. Charred weapon racks and melted armor stands line the
walls. A few items remain intact, protected by some enchantment that also
seems to be slowly consuming them. The floor is covered in ash several
inches deep that stirs despite the absence of wind.
~
