The symbols on the ceiling are not the same as the runes elsewhere in
Kel'Shadra. They are older, cruder - suggesting this part of the keep
was built before the void entity arrived, by the original mortal builders.
~
S

#625
The Hall of Echoes~
A long corridor whose walls are pocked with small alcoves, each containing
a different object: a cracked bell, a fractured mirror, a dried flower, a
child's toy. Each object produces a faint echo when the room is entered, as
if whispering of the person who last touched it. The combined effect is a
constant low murmur that follows you throughout the hall.
~
