The Sorcerer's Refuge~
A hidden room that can only be found by those who paid attention to
all the environmental clues throughout the citadel. Once a private
study of a sorcerer who served Kel'Shadra before realizing his mistake,
this room contains research notes, personal items, and most crucially,
tactical advice for confronting the void entity.
~
8201 11
D3
~
~
0 -1 672
E study notes research sorcerer advice~
The sorcerer's notes are extensive and well-organized despite being
centuries old. The critical section is titled 'Weaknesses of the Void':
apparently the entity can be damaged significantly more effectively
if attacked while it is maintaining one of its secondary abilities.
The notes also mention that the sorcerer hid his best weapons here.
~
S

#702
The Memory Pool~
A perfectly circular pool of dark water in a hidden alcove. Those who
drink from it experience a vivid vision - not of the past, but of the
most important moment in their own future. The vision is accurate but
may be difficult to interpret. The pool has one cost: a small portion
of the drinker's life force, permanently given.
~
8201 11
D1
~
~
0 -1 625
E pool water vision memory~
The pool's surface is absolutely still. Looking into it, you can see
your own reflection clearly - but it changes, aging rapidly, then
reversing, then stopping at a specific moment. The pool shows you
something you will do. Whether it is a warning or a gift depends
entirely on what you do with the knowledge.
~
S

